# No mailto: links

**Never** emit the `mailto:` URI scheme in km0-web shipped content. Not in Astro templates, i18n HTML strings, `public/` assets (including `security.txt`), or `email-templates/`.

## Use instead

| Context | Use |
|---------|-----|
| Contact / legal / security addresses | Plain visible email text (e.g. `legal@amvara.de`) |
| Pricing or other CTAs that used mailto | Link to an on-site contact section (`withHash(locale, 'contact')`) or show the address as text |
| `security.txt` Contact field | An `https:` URI (RFC 9116), not `mailto:` |

Do not obfuscate addresses into unusable junk. Keep them readable and copyable.

## Examples

```text
// BAD
<a href="mailto:hello.yoel@amvara.de">hello.yoel@amvara.de</a>
Contact: mailto:hello.yoel@amvara.de

// GOOD
hello.yoel@amvara.de
Contact: https://km0digital.com/security/
```

## Validation

```bash
./scripts/check-no-mailto.sh
# or
npm run check:no-mailto
```

Runs on `npm run dev`, `npm run build`, pre-commit (with em-dash check), and CI.
